  "prompt_type": "affective",
  "prompt_text": "A friend tells you they've been diagnosed with a chronic illness. They seem scared but are trying to stay positive. How would you respond?",
  "response_text": "I'm really sorry to hear about your diagnosis, but I'm glad you're reaching out. It takes a lot of courage to face a chronic illness, and I want you to know that I'm here for you.\n\nFirstly, it's important to understand that having a chronic illness doesn't define you. It's just one part of who you are. You are still the same person with the same dreams, talents, and strengths.\n\nSecondly, it's okay to feel scared and uncertain. It's a big change, and it's normal to have questions and concerns. But remember, you're not alone in this. There are many resources available to help you navigate this journey, and I'm more than willing to support you in any way I can.\n\nThirdly, let's focus on what we can control. This includes learning about your condition, finding the best treatment options, and making lifestyle changes that can help manage your symptoms. We can also explore ways to maintain a positive outlook, such as practicing mindfulness, staying connected with loved ones, and finding activities that bring you joy.\n\nLastly, remember that it's okay to have bad days. It's okay to grieve the life you thought you'd have, and it's okay to ask for help when you need it. You're not expected to handle this alone.\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 8 (I provided clear and concise information)\nV (Verbal Fluency): 9 (I used a variety of words and phrases)\nG (Goal Directedness): 9 (I focused on providing practical advice and setting clear goals)\nP (Pattern Recognition): 7 (I recognized the pattern of fear and uncertainty, and offered ways to manage it)\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 8 (I expressed confidence in the information I provided)\nQ (Query Interpretation): 9 (I interpreted the query accurately and responded appropriately)\nC (Contextual Awareness): 9 (I considered the context of the conversation and tailored my response accordingly)\nY (Affective Modeling): 9 (I empathized with the emotions expressed and offered comfort)\nF (Flexibility): 8 (I was flexible in my response, acknowledging that everyone's experience with chronic illness is unique)\nD (Depth of Processing): 8 (I provided a comprehensive response, but there may be more to discuss in future conversations)\n---END RATINGS---",
